    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini Dei salvatoris Iesu Christi. Concessimus nos <rs
                            key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">vir gloriosissimus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Princeps #Patricius" ref="#people/90">Guaimarius</persName>
                        Dei providentia <rs key="#Princeps">Langobardorum gentis princeps</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Patricius">inperialis patricius</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/298">Guaimarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs> eius, <rs key="#Intercessory">per rogum</rs>
                        <persName key="#Medical_doctors #Prevosts #Personal_rank #fidelisOf"><name
                                ref="Rainfredus">Ragemfrid</name>
                        </persName><rs key="#Medical_doctors #Society">medici</rs> e <rs
                            key="#Prevosts #rectorOf">prepositi</rs>, in <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots" ref="#juridical_persons/84">Sancti
                            Benedicti</orgName> de <rs key="#Castle">castro</rs> Casino, ubi nunc
                        domnus <persName key="#Abbots"><name ref="Ragibrandus"
                            >Ragemprandus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> regimen tenere videtur, integras ipsas <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Property_of_persons_without_heirs"
                            ref="#estates/242">res</rs> que fuit <persName
                            key="#Property_of_persons_without_heirs"><name ref="Leo"
                            >Leonis</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Property_of_persons_without_heirs"><name ref="Ursus"
                            >Ursi</name></persName>, seu et res <persName
                            key="#Property_of_persons_without_heirs"><name ref="Ragibrandus"
                                >Ragemprandi</name></persName> et res Leonis et res <persName
                            key="#Property_of_persons_without_heirs"><name ref="Radipertus"
                                >Radiperti</name></persName>, qui <rs
                            key="#Property_of_persons_without_heirs">sine heredibus</rs> mortui
                        sunt, cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >casis et omnia illorum pertinentia</rs> ubique exinde fuerit inventus,
                        sicut <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Redistributive"
                            >sacro nostro Palatio pertinet</rs>, hec omnia de <rs key="#Actio"
                            >acto</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Actio"
                            ref="#places/540">Rotense</placeName>, in e videlicet ratione ut amodo
                        et deinceps per hoc nostrorum roboreum <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">preceptum</rs> ea que supra
                        legitur, totum in eodem sancto monasterio permaneat, eius rectoribus
                        dominandum et habendum firmiter, et a nullo ex nostris iudicibus, id est
                        comitibus, castaldeis vel a <rs key="#agentFor">quibuscumque agentibus</rs>
                        habeatis aliquam requisitionis, set perpetuo tempore possideatis. Quod vera
                        preceptum concessionis ex iussione supradicte potestatis scripsi ego
                            <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Deusdedit"
                            >Deusdedit</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer #Notary">notarius sacri Palatii</rs>. Actum
                            <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/84">Salernu</placeName> vicesimu
                        primo anno, mense Augusto, quintadecima indictione feliciter. <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals #Property_of_persons_without_heirs"
                            ref="#estates/242">Curtes</geogName> vero has tenet <persName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals #Estate_supervisors #Property_of_persons_without_heirs"
                                ><name ref="Lupus">Lupus</name>
                            <name ref="Magaricus">Magaricus</name></persName>, que fuit curtem
                        Leonis et Ursi et Ragemprandi, Leonis et Radiperti, et singuli curtes suas
                        habuerunt et fuerunt <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">castaldani</rs>
                        <persName key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus"><name ref="Rodelgardus"
                                >Rodelgardi</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus"><name ref="Maio"
                            >Maiionis</name></persName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>Voigt 1902, n. 86.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p>Bloch 1986, pp. 781, 1347.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>I principi Guaimario I e II concedono a Montecassino e all’abate Ragemprando i
                    beni di Leo, Orso, Ragemprando, Leo e Radiperto, morti senza eredi, siti
                        nell’<foreign>actus Rotensis</foreign> e ora detenuti da Magarico. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
